<Content>Expatriots forging common bonds I quite literally stumbled upon the Hotel Crystal on arrival in Berlin. The Hotel is centrally located, in Savigny Platz about a 10 minute walk from the Ku-Dam and 5 minutes from the S-Bahn. We had a room on the top floor with balcony facing the tree-lined street. Very quiet, unassuming and gem眉tlich. We felt very much at home with our British concierge, Scottish bar friends, and other traveling Americans. If you like a bit of the old world (think Cold War spy movies), you'll love the ambience here. Book well in advance! 
